ability.title.satsu.clavar.escudo: Plant the shield on the ground
ability.title.satsu.part.head: Helmet
ability.title.satsu.part.throw.head: Throw Helmet
To put on mark 1 to 3 you need to create this block to put on the armor
advancements.satsu_iron_man_addon.ia.tar: Build an AI card for better functionality in your armor
advancements.satsu_iron_man_addon.more.d: You can unlock even more armor...
advancements.satsu_iron_man_addon.reacto: Build an arc energy block on to charge if you need it
description.Energy.Pulse: By activating this the armor will be able to throw energy from the hands (with right or left click, when you click you can choose to use one or both)
description.ark.upgrade.thing.1: By unlocking this the Arc reactor will recharge itself and will not overcharge so as not to damage you
description.ark.upgrade.thing.2: By unlocking this the Arc reactor will recharge itself and will not overcharge so as not to damage you when you are using the armor
description.armor_skill_bar: This is your skill tree; To start you will have a limit of 10000 energy with which to use armor, wearing it or using abilities will spend more energy, on the top screen you will see an icon which will change color depending on your energy (orange is when it's full); To unlock more armors you will have to keep using them and to recharge you will need to use a powered arc energy block
description.energy_beam: Launch an energy beam from your Arc reactor
description.flight: When you have some armor in place you will have the ability to fly
description.flight.mark.1: Being your first armor you won't have the ability to fly completely
description.force_field: With the energy of your armor create a shield to block enemy attacks
description.ia_skill_stat: This is the skill tree that will allow you to unlock your various IA functions
description.iron.man.aquatic_breath: When you use the helmet activated you will be able to breathe underwater
description.iron.man.class.danger.contro: This type of armor is characterized by its pincers to grab entities
description.iron.man.class.exo: This type of armor is characterized by the fact that it can be worn under any suit (limiting the use of its abilities to a simple common suit) but providing a little more resistance, cushioning, and strength, consuming a lot of energy
description.iron.man.class.heartbreaker: This type of armor is characterized by its more powerful chest arc beam; at the same time it has a long cooldown for this and uses less energy
description.iron.man.class.multi_functio: This type of armor is characterized by the ability to use different attachments on the armor, such as hammers, vibranium claws, flamethrowers, among other things
description.iron.man.class.nanotech: This type of armor is characterized by being able to create weapons and various things, as well as being more portable and able to activate at any time
description.iron.man.class.silver.centur: This type of armor is characterized by having retractable daggers and striking colors
description.iron.man.class.speed: This type of armor is characterized by a great increase in flight speed and leaves a trail when you run or fly
description.iron.man.class.stealth: This type of armor is characterized by the ability to become invisible
description.iron.man.class.striker: This type of armor is characterized by having prehensile hammers with which you can break the ground more easily, as well as having the ability to drill or make a strong attack with the hammers
description.iron.man.extremis.beam.1: Focus your inner fire in your hands to launch an energy beam (6 damage) (To unlock it in the skill bar you need to activate the fire fists)
description.iron.man.extremis.beam.2: Increase the damage level of the beam (12 damage)  (To unlock it in the skill bar you need to activate the fire fists)
description.iron.man.extremis.beam.3: Turns what you touch into lava  (To unlock it in the skill bar you need to activate the fire fists)
description.iron.man.extremis.fire.punch: Focus your inner fire in your hands to burn anyone you hit
description.iron.man.extremis.mouth.1: Focus your inner fire in your throat to launch an energy beam (12 damage)
description.iron.man.extremis.mouth.2: Increase the damage level of the beam (15 damage)
description.iron.man.fire_resistance: With the armor equipped you are resistant to fire
description.iron.man.mark.1: Mark 1 is your first armor, it has flamethrowers and a launchable missile; With your boots you have the ability to fly but not for long or at great heights (to put it on you need to create an armor placement block) Durability:15    Strength: 1
description.iron.man.mark.10: Mark 10 is a successor to mark 9, has a greater flight system, with more speed while being an underwater breathing prototype, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:22    Strength: 9    Flight Speed: 6.25
description.iron.man.mark.11: The Mark 11 is a prototype of stealth class armors, its camouflage lasts a short time, uses the gripping system of the Mark 7 Durability:22    Strength: 6    Flight speed: 6.15
description.iron.man.mark.12: Mark 12 is one of the first War Machine prototypes, It has a black and silver design, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:22    Strength: 9    Flight Speed: 6.15
description.iron.man.mark.13: The Mark 13 is another prototype War Machine. It has a black and silver design and is lighter than its predecessors, increasing its flight speed. You can choose whether to use the minigun in your hand or the typical plasma shots. It uses the Mark 7's prensil system and has a flare. Durability: 22    Strength: 9    Flight speed: 6.35
description.iron.man.mark.14: Mark 14 is another War Machine prototype, It has a black and silver design, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:22    Strength: 10    Flight Speed: 6.25
description.iron.man.mark.15: Mark 15 known as Sneaky is a stealth class armor, It has a black and silver design; camouflage duration is now longer while having a sonic tranquilization system, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:22    Strength: 10    Flight Speed: 6.25
description.iron.man.mark.17: The Mark 17 known as Heartbreaker is the first Heartbreaker class armor, uses the gripping system of the Mark 7 /Has flare/ Durability:22    Strength: 10    Flight speed: 6.25
description.iron.man.mark.18: The Mark 18, known as Cassanova, is another Heartbreaker-class armor along with the Stealth class. It has the same camouflage system as its predecessors, color change, and, like the Mark 13, you can switch between using the minigun or conventional plasma shots. It uses the Mark 7's prensil system and has a flare. Durability: 23    Strength: 11    Flight speed: 6.25
description.iron.man.mark.1873: An armor made of nanotechnology with steampunk appearance (With smoke abilities) Durability:43    Strength: 46    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.19.tiger: Mark 19 known as Tiger is the first prototype of fast flight armors, this type is characterized by the ability to fly faster and have a trail of the same color as the armor, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:23    Strength: 8    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.2: Mark 2 is primarily a flight prototype although it doesn't reach much height, it has plasma bursts and a chest uni-beam (to put it on you need to create an armor placement block) Durability:15    Strength: 1    Flight Speed: 6
description.iron.man.mark.20: Mark 20 known as Python, Has a black and gold design is the successor to mark 19, similarly is a fast flight armor, having the black and gold color trail, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:23    Strength: 12    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.21.midas: Mark 21 known as Midas, Has a totally gold design based on mark 7, is completely gold, while being characterized as a fast flight armor, like its brothers of this type it has the characteristic trail and increased flight capability, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:24    Strength: 6    Flight Speed: 6.65
description.iron.man.mark.22: Mark 22 known as Hotrod is a War Machine armor, with a peculiar design based on the hotrod car, Has miniguns on each forearm, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:24    Strength: 12    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.23: The Mark 23 known as Shades, has a spotted design, is a stealth class armor, and is fire resistant, uses the gripping system of the Mark 7 /Has flare/ Durability:24    Strength: 12    Flight speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.24: The Mark 24 known as Tank is a Heartbreaker class armor, uses the gripping system of the Mark 7 /Has flare/ Durability:24    Strength: 13    Flight speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.25: Mark 25 known as Striker is the first of a new class, has two prehensile hammers with which you can break ground more easily, besides having the ability to drill or make a strong attack with the hammers, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:24    Strength: 13    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.26: Mark 26 known as Gamma is the successor to mark 25, has two prehensile hammers with which you can break ground more easily, besides having the ability to drill or make a strong attack with the hammers, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:24    Strength: 13    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.27: Mark 27 known as Disco Has a peculiar color pattern based on disco balls, while being stealth class, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:24    Strength: 14    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.28: Mark 28 known as Jack is the successor to mark 27, Has a peculiar color pattern based on disco balls like its predecessor, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:24    Strength: 14    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.29: The Mark 29 known as Fiddler is a Heartbreaker class armor, uses the gripping system of the Mark 7 /Has flare/ Durability:24    Strength: 15    Flight speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.3: Mark 3, by changing material eliminates flight restrictions reaching more height (to put it on you need to create an armor placement block) /Has flare/ Durability:20    Strength: 3    Flight Speed: 6
description.iron.man.mark.30: Mark 30 known as Blue steel is the first of the silver centurion series models, Has a light blue and silver design, Has retractable vibranium daggers for close combat, Additionally they are capable of mining, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:25    Strength: 16    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.31: Mark 31 known as Piston is the second armor of the silver centurion series models, Has a green and silver design, this unlike its brothers is a fast flight armor, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:25    Strength: 17    Flight Speed: 6.75
description.iron.man.mark.32: Mark 32 known as Romeo is the definitive version of Heartbreaker armors, Has a black and silver design, while having fast flight, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:25    Strength: 18    Flight Speed: 6.65
description.iron.man.mark.33: Mark 33 known as Silver centurion is the third armor of the Silver centurion series, Has a red and silver design, like blue steel has retractable vibranium daggers that are capable of mining, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:25    Strength: 18    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.34: Mark 34 known as Southpaw is the first of the Disaster Rescue armors, its design is quite similar to mark 14 and has a claw that allows it to grab entities to carry them or throw them away, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:24    Strength: 19    Flight Speed: 6.25
description.iron.man.mark.35: Mark 35 known as Red Snapper is the second of the Disaster Rescue armors, its design retains the typical red with yellow and silver colors; Has dual claws that allow it to grab entities to carry them or throw them away, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:25    Strength: 20    Flight Speed: 6.25
description.iron.man.mark.36: Mark 36 known as Peacemaker is the third of the Disaster Rescue armors, its design is the same as the Red Snapper armor with the difference of orange, silver and black colors; Like mark 15 sneaky has sonic tranquilizers, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:26    Strength: 21    Flight Speed: 6.15
description.iron.man.mark.37: Mark 37 known as Hammerhead is the direct successor to mark 10, which had underwater breathing, has an aquamarine design with gold and various underwater capabilities as well as improved swimming in a unique way and a repulsor shield, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:27    Strength: 22    Flight Speed: 6.45
description.iron.man.mark.38: Mark 38 known as Igor is a unique class armor, With a blue and silver design, Capable of lifting heavy things like mobs and crushing them, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:28    Strength: 23    Flight Speed: 6.05
description.iron.man.mark.39: Mark 39 known as Starboost is an armor designed to travel between planets (Only available with Ad astra or Cosmic Horizons), uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:29    Strength: 25    Flight Speed: 6.65
description.iron.man.mark.4: The Mark 4 is the successor to the Mark 3. Its design is basically the same but with a lighter red color. Durability: 20    Strength: 3    Flight speed: 6
description.iron.man.mark.40: Mark 40 known as Shotgun is the final version of fast flight armors, having a great increase in this while like its brothers has the characteristic trail, uses mark 7's prehensile system /Has flare/ Durability:28    Strength: 8    Flight Speed: 6.85
description.iron.man.mark.41: Mark 41, known as Bones, is a prototype of a new class of armors with separated pieces, which will join you when you call them. It has the ability to throw its pieces at an enemy to deal damage. Durability:30    Strength: 13    Flight Speed: 6.85
description.iron.man.mark.42: Mark 42, known as Prodigal Son, has the characteristics of its predecessors, such as heat resistance, underwater breathing, and space travel (Only available with Ad Astra or Cosmic Horizons). It also features increased speed and reduced energy consumption for the chest repulsor. Like its predecessor, it is an armor capable of splitting into parts and can be called either fully or in specific parts. Durability:32    Strength: 14.5    Flight Speed: 6.85
description.iron.man.mark.42-b: Mark 42-b, known as SDCA, has the characteristics of its predecessors, such as heat resistance, underwater breathing, and space travel (Only available with Ad Astra or Cosmic Horizons). It also features increased speed and reduced energy consumption for the chest repulsor. Like its predecessor, it is an armor capable of splitting into parts and can be called either fully or in specific parts. Durability:32    Strength: 14.5    Flight Speed: 6.85
description.iron.man.mark.43: The Mark 43, known as Prodigal Son Plus, is the direct successor to Prodigal Son and possesses the same characteristics, such as heat resistance, underwater breathing, and space travel (Only available with Ad Astra or Cosmic Horizons). It also features increased speed and reduced energy consumption for the chest repulsor. Like its predecessor, it is an armor capable of splitting into parts and can be called either fully or in specific parts. Durability:34    Strength: 16.5    Flight Speed: 6.85
description.iron.man.mark.45: The Mark 45 is the successor to the Mark 43. It has the gripping system of the Mark 42, but is more resistant and stronger. /It has a flare./ Durability: 35    Strength: 30    Flight speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.46: Mark 46 is a successor to Mark 45, featuring a different system than most of its predecessors. It is designed for confined spaces like a briefcase and is equipped with repulsors, missiles, flares, an electromagnetic pulse, and a sonic tranquilizer. Durability:36    Strength: 16.5    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.47: Mark 47 is the direct successor to Mark 46, featuring the same confinement system and is used in a briefcase. It has a basic weapon system, with missiles and flares Durability:37    Strength: 32    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.5: Mark 5 is the first portable armor; although weaker than its predecessors, it's carried in a briefcase Durability:10    Strength: 4    Flight Speed: 6
description.iron.man.mark.50: Mark 50 is the first armor made of nanotechnology, has retractable daggers, two different swords, a shield and several more upgrades Durability:40    Strength: 37    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.6: Mark 6 is the direct successor to mark 5, It has a red and silver design, although this one is no longer carried in a briefcase it has a sentinel with a prehensile system with which you can join to wear the armor /Has flare/ Durability:20    Strength: 2    Flight Speed: 6
description.iron.man.mark.7: Mark 7 is a successor to mark 6, with improvements in strength and durability while having the same prehensile system as mark 7 /Has flare/ Durability:21    Strength: 8    Flight Speed: 6
description.iron.man.mark.8: Mark 8 is a successor to mark 7, with improvements in strength and durability while having the same prehensile system as mark 7 /Has flare/ Durability:21    Strength: 8    Flight Speed: 6
description.iron.man.mark.80: Mark 80 is a nanotechnology armor with a red design with gray and gold accents. It has retractable daggers, two different swords, a shield and several more upgrades Durability:40    Strength: 37    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.81: Mark 81 is a nanotechnology armor with a red and gold design with gray accents. It has retractable daggers, two different swords, a shield and several more upgrades Durability:40    Strength: 37    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.82: The Mark 82 is a nanotechnology suit with a silver and red design. It has retractable daggers, two different swords, a shield, and several other upgrades, as well as sonic tranquilizers to aid in combat. Durability: 40    Strength: 37    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.85: Mark 85 is a nanotechnology armor with a gold and red design with gray accents. It has retractable daggers, two different swords, a shield and several more upgrades Durability:40    Strength: 37    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.9: Mark 9 is the prototype of mark 10, which is an armor that slightly improves speed while having the same prehensile system as mark 7 Durability:22    Strength: 8    Flight Speed: 6.15
description.iron.man.mark.Iron.destroyer: A uru armor that has magical properties /Has luck, jump and water agility effects/ Durability:40    Strength: 38    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.Stealh: Mark 16 known as Nightclub is a stealth class armor, camouflage duration is designed for its use, has a color change system at night and day, uses mark 7's prehensile system Durability:22    Strength: 3    Flight Speed: 6.25
description.iron.man.mark.extremis: A nanotechnology armor made with the extremis virus Durability:68    Strength: 27.5    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.model.prime: A nanotechnology armor capable of customization Durability:44    Strength: 38    Flight Speed: 6.57
description.iron.man.mark.taken: Nanotech armor with a unique design and capabilities such as teleportation and access to a Hulkbuster. Durability: 65    Strength: 55    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.mark.unknow.blooded: Enchanted nanotechnology armor to fight against vampires (slows enemies with its plasma projectiles, besides being able to advance time, slow it down or stop it) Durability:45    Strength: 46    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.model.nil: An armor made for total stealth, equipped with tasers to paralyze and the ability to pass through walls. Durability:32    Strength: 14.2    Flight Speed: 6.57
description.iron.man.projectile_resistan: With the armor equipped you are resistant to projectiles
description.iron.man.superior.armor: An endosymbiotic armor, quite strong, capable of launching energy beams to paralyze enemies (You need to craft a metalized symbiote to unlock it) Durability:65    Strength: 47    Flight Speed: 6.55
description.iron.man.symbiote_metalized: A symbiote made of metal capable of enhancing your abilities.
description.iron.man.war_machine.mark.1: The modified Mark 2 is more resistant than the original version and has more weapons, such as miniguns on its arms, a turret, grenade launchers, and several missiles. This armor is placed in the gantry station, just like the Mark 4. Durability: 17    Strength: 5.5    Flight speed: 6
description.satsu.accelerate.time: Accelerate time making you faster (Includes enemies)
description.satsu.additamens.energy_cano: summons enhancers to launch several powerful energy beams
description.satsu.additamens.flame.throw: You can use flamethrowers to burn your enemies for quite some time with the yellow and black cartridges
description.satsu.ark.beam.for.hands: You can toggle between energy pulses and a single Arc beam, activated with the same button (right or left click) (you can toggle between seeing this button or configuring your armor by crouching)
description.satsu.ark.upgrade.max.energy: You can upgrade the Arc reactor to have more energy (20000 maximum)
You can upgrade the Arc reactor even further to have more energy (80000 maximum)
With this upgrade, the arc reactor will recharge itself when you are not wearing armor
description.satsu.ark.upgrade.portable.m: You can upgrade the Arc reactor to have more energy (130000 maximum)
You can upgrade the Arc reactor even further to have more energy (80000 maximum)
With this upgrade, the arc reactor will recharge itself when you are not wearing armor
description.satsu.ark_upgrades: This is an upgrade branch of your Arc reactor
description.satsu.armor.branch: This is a branch of basic/passive armor abilities
description.satsu.armor.edit: With this ability you can see the menu to choose armor, activate life insurance and perform other actions
description.satsu.arms.edit: When activating this ability you can choose extra weapons, such as rockets, swords and more (You need to activate the armor edit ability)
description.satsu.break.off.on: By activating or deactivating this option, some attacks may break blocks, such as the max pulse or mining with striker armor
description.satsu.choose.armor: When activating this ability you can choose which armor to put on (You need to activate the armor edit ability)
description.satsu.clap_smoke_hands: Creates a smoke area to suffocate your enemies for 15 seconds
description.satsu.color.change.mode: You can change the armor color by pressing the button or it will automatically change at night
description.satsu.config_gui: You can configure the HUD view mode
description.satsu.config_gui_additional_: Configure whether or not to have additional images in the HUD
description.satsu.config_gui_horizon_loc: You can turn off/on the horizon lock of the HUD
description.satsu.dampened.sound: Use your sonic weaponry to pacify enemies (Slows them down, leaving them immobile)
description.satsu.dampened.sound.additam: You can use sonic weapons to tranquilize enemies (slowing them down and rendering them immobile) with black and white cartridges
description.satsu.dampeneed: This damper is used to block abilities with the arc reactor
description.satsu.decrease.speed: Use this skill to decrease flight speed
description.satsu.disable.sentinel: When you have armor acting by itself you can put it back on
description.satsu.dril.ground: Use the hammers to drill the ground for a limited time; This action will cause damage and break the blocks if you have this option active
description.satsu.durability: Receives a durability increase with diferents armors
description.satsu.emp: Activates the ability to emit an electromagnetic pulse that neutralizes other armor (or technological devices with the dampened mod)
description.satsu.enable.sentinel: Having an included AI you can make your armor act by itself by removing it from you
description.satsu.ex.wife: Use the skill to launch a powerfull misil (15 damage)
description.satsu.extremis.durability: Thanks to the extremis virus you have an increase in resistance (10 points)
description.satsu.extremis.durability.po: Thanks to the extremis virus you have increased damage resistance (3.5 points)
description.satsu.extremis.healing: Thanks to the extremis virus you are able to regenerate

Increase your regeneration ability (0.4 hearts within 3 seconds)
Increase your regeneration ability (0.5 hearts within 5 seconds)
Increase your regeneration ability (0.8 hearts within 10 seconds)
description.satsu.extremis.jump: Thanks to the extremis virus you have an increase in jump (0.25 points/1.5 blocks)
description.satsu.extremis.jump.1: Increase your jump resistance (0.1 points/2 blocks)
description.satsu.extremis.jump.2: Increase your jump resistance (0.1 points/2.5 blocks)
description.satsu.extremis.jump.3: Increase your jump resistance (0.1 points/3 blocks)
description.satsu.extremis.power: The extremis virus is a modification of your DNA with nanotechnology, granting you several additional abilities
description.satsu.extremis.strength: Thanks to the extremis virus you have an increase in strength (8 points)
description.satsu.extremis.strength.powe: Thanks to the extremis virus you have an increase in strength (1 point)
Increase your strength with the extremis virus (1.5 points)
Increase your strength with the extremis virus (1 point)
Increase your strength with the extremis virus (1 point)
description.satsu.failsafe.edit: When activating this ability you can enable/disable the armor's ability to save you when you are hurt (You need to activate the armor edit ability)
description.satsu.fall_resistance: You are quite resistant to falls
description.satsu.flare.flame: Use the flares to blind opponents if it is a player, mobs will be immobilized for a while
description.satsu.flight.edit: When activating this ability you can increase/decrease flight speed (You need to activate the armor edit ability)
description.satsu.give.recipe: Right click to get the armor blueprints
description.satsu.grab_cannon: Turn your hand into a cannon, which can paralyze your enemies when fired (takes a while to charge, you can shoot 4 times and deals 12 damage)
description.satsu.grenade.launcher: Use the ability to throw multiple grenades at the ground
description.satsu.ground.attack: With your hammers you can do a ground attack, break blocks and launch your enemies into the air
description.satsu.handle: With right click you can remove your arc reactor from your chest
description.satsu.health: Receives a health increase with diferents armors
description.satsu.ia.choose: Activate this to move to the next or previous AI; each AI will treat you differently and have different interactions
description.satsu.ia.color: Each AI has a characteristic color
description.satsu.ia.gui: It's just your AI's icon on screen
description.satsu.ia.night.vision: With your AI you have the ability to activate night vision using the voice command or the wheel
description.satsu.ia.scan.abilitie: This is part of the enemy scanning ability branch, you can unlock it to activate it
description.satsu.ia_tarjet: This empty card can be filled with an AI with different names, which will help you by having some extra improvements, such as warning you when you have low energy among others
description.satsu.igor_crash: When you grab a player or entity, you can crush them (deals 45 damage)
description.satsu.igor_grab: You can grab entities or players with this ability, you can also throw them away
description.satsu.increase.speed: Use this skill to increase flight speed
description.satsu.intangibility: When you activate the ability, you will be able to pass through walls and blocks
description.satsu.light_flash: Activates the ability to cast a flash of light to blind nearby enemies (5 blocks)
description.satsu.metodo.de.colocacion.b: When you have the entire armor activated, you will need an armor placement block to be able to activate the armor's functions
description.satsu.metodo.de.colocacion.g: With this system, the armor is placed on top of the gantry station and can only be placed/removed there
description.satsu.metodo.de.colocacion.l: With this system, the armor can be called to you, either in pieces or as a whole.
description.satsu.metodo.de.colocacion.m: With this system, the armor is equipped when you enter a sentinel. You can call a sentinel at any time if you haven't already.
description.satsu.metodo.de.colocacion.n: With this system, the armor can be equipped at any time and in any situation.
description.satsu.minigun: This armor is capable of deploying mini gun to fire bullets instead of the repulsor when necessary; you can choose it within the weapon wheel
description.satsu.nano.drone: When you activate this ability, you will build a nano drone that fires at regular intervals when you do, or when you use a combat ability
description.satsu.nano.health.spray: Use a spray to seal wounds and recover more easily
description.satsu.nano.health.spray.othe: Use a spray to seal wounds and help other players recover more easily
description.satsu.nano.weapons: You can choose which weapons and abilities to use; you can use three different firing systems and/or different weapons
description.satsu.nano_grenade_launcher: Create a grenade launcher made of nanotechnology from your hand (increases damage by 5 points, and you can only shoot 3 every 30 seconds)
description.satsu.nano_hand_blade: Create a nanotechnology sword from your hand (increases damage by 4 points)
description.satsu.nano_mallet: Create nanotechnology hammers from your hands (increases damage by 4 points)
description.satsu.nano_rial: Create a nanotechnology minigun from your hand (increases damage by 2 points and fires twice)
description.satsu.one.rocket: Launch a rocket from your hand (15 damage)
description.satsu.pickaxe.velocity: While wearing armor, your mining speed increases (Varies depending on the armor)
description.satsu.pincher_both: You can easily grab entities with both hands when close to them, you can also throw them with left click
description.satsu.pincher_left: You can easily grab entities with your left hand when close to them, you can also throw them with left click
description.satsu.pincher_right: You can easily grab entities with your right hand when close to them, you can also throw them with left click
description.satsu.recipe_table: Here you can find the blueprints to create your armors
description.satsu.red.mini.beams: Use this ability to launch thinner red mini beams that deal more damage
description.satsu.red.mini.beams.additam: You can use red rays to easily mine blocks with black and red cartridges
description.satsu.remote.mode: With the AI glasses you can activate the remote mode to control your armor remotely. To activate, type remote on in the chat and to deactivate, remote off
description.satsu.remove.ia: You can easily remove the AI by clicking on the ability, depending on the AI you have, it will give you a different card
description.satsu.remove.ia_glases: You can remove the glasses by clicking on the ability
description.satsu.reroute: When you start the voice command you can reroute the energy to: Thrusters (to have double speed, although you will consume double the energy)
description.satsu.sentinel: You can activate a sentinel armor either with voice commands or the skill wheel, which will follow you and help you fight
description.satsu.shotgun: When you use the skill, you will have shotgun mode, which does more damage but has a very short range
description.satsu.sonic.clap: Use this ability to perform a sonic clap, damaging enemies and launching them two blocks away (You can break blocks)
description.satsu.stabilizer: With the stabilizers you will be faster and better at flying
description.satsu.strength: Receives a strength increase with diferents armors
description.satsu.taken.aoe.damage: Use the taken power of the armor to deal area damage
description.satsu.taken.hulkbuster: Increase your size to that of a hulkbuster while increasing your strength
description.satsu.taser_charge: When you activate the ability, you will be able to charge a taser to paralyze your enemies
description.satsu.throw.blades: You can activate or deactivate the vibranium daggers to do more damage or achieve an attack with them
description.satsu.throw.blades.attack: With the vibranium daggers perform an attack with which you can attack several enemies at once
description.satsu.throw.smoke: Throws smoke to suffocate your enemies
description.satsu.time.clock: Completely pause time, making enemies unable to move
description.satsu.torpedos: Use this ability to launch torpedoes underwater
description.satsu.tourret: Use the skill to activate/deactivate the turret (This is used when firing or right/left-clicking with active weapons)
description.satsu.trail.off.on: By clicking the ability you can enable or disable the trail on speed class armors
description.satsu.unlock.lock.ia.gui: You can enable/disable this to see your AI on screen
description.satsu.unlock.lock.ia.gui.ene: Having the AI now you can see exactly how much energy you have
description.satsu.unlock.lock.ia.scan.ab: If you have the abilities menu disabled you can enable/disable the scan ability
description.satsu.unlock.lock.ia.sentine: If you have the abilities menu disabled you can enable/disable the ability to use a sentinel armor
description.satsu.unlock.lock.ia.skill.t: By clicking on the ability you can deactivate the AI menu, so it interferes less
description.satsu.voice.comands.ia: You can type your AI's name to ask it to perform some actions, which are as follows: Sentinel (to activate a sentinel). Vision: to activate night vision. Scan: to scan for enemies. Remote on: to activate remote mode (only with AI glasses). Remote off: to deactivate remote mode (only with AI glasses). Reroute: (with various functions, which are described in the other ability)
description.satsu.water.movement: This ability will be available underwater, allowing you to swim faster
description.satsu.wings: Deploy wings to gain more speed and flight control
description.superior.electrokinesis: Paralyze your enemies with a bolt of electricity
description.superior.suit.expulsion: Ejects part of the suit to damage enemies
description.superior.telekinesis: By using the ability you will be able to grab objects on the ground and enemies with your mind
item.satsu_iron_man_addon.steel_gold_all: Raw steel and gold alloy ingot
item.satsu_iron_man_addon.steel_gold_ref: Refined steel and gold alloy ingot
satsu.iron.man.addon.text.earned.points: You have earned an experience point for the armors
